author: Responsible-Buy6015
body: A lower fed rate and higher tariffs both increase inflationary pressure.  The fed needs to see how many tariffs actually take effect, how severe they are, and what impact that has on the economy before doing anything.  And if they do react, the correct response will almost certainly not be to lower the fed rate as that would increase inflation.
